0.1.14: Discord-style call banner + native OS notifications + dialing sound

Call UI:
- Replaced floating bottom-right call bar with a Discord-style banner pinned
  to the top of the DM messages area. Mute / Deafen / Leave buttons live in
  the banner; clicking the peer area jumps back to the DM the call is in.
- Live mm:ss duration counter once connected.

Bug fix: call window not closing reliably
- The previous "show reason text for 1.5s then hide" had no way to cancel a
  pending hide. Successive teardowns + new calls could leave the banner
  visible. Now hide / tick timers are tracked and cancelled on every show
  and every teardown.

Notifications:
- Dropped the in-app toast UI in favor of native OS notifications via the
  Notification API. Shows a real Windows toast outside the app window;
  click to focus + open the DM. We pass silent:true so the OS doesn't ding
  on top of our own sound.
- New notification sound: Notify.mp3 (replaces the prior dragon-studio one).
- Permission is requested lazily on first notification.

Audio cues:
- New dialing.mp3 plays in a loop while an outgoing call is ringing
  (state = inviting). Stops as soon as the callee accepts, declines, or
  the call ends.
- Incoming call now plays the notification sound + flashes the taskbar
  alongside the modal so callees notice when the window isn't focused.

